				<td colspan="2"><span>Still soloable.  
<br />

<br />
I followed the advice on the area to kite.  Great writeup. Basically stay west of the pipe water runoffs.  There's like 3 of them north to south.  For the first pass I loaded up Kazumi's to try to round up the three east most stonemites but only two of them agroed.  The third one agroed sometime in the middle of the kite.  The stonemites have an extremely small assist/agro range.  
<br />

<br />
This is a straight forward but extremely boring chant kite.  I generally saw the stonemites drop 2% per tick.  The AK dropped 1% per tick.  That's with 4 chants, TDoK, IM4, and JF3.  With the stonemites I also dropped Anglich's Assonance, but this won't land on the AK since he's immune to slow.  I don't have the crit DoT AAs yet as I hardly ever chant kite anymore.  I suppose a suicidal AoE kiter could try all nine stonemites at once but I never got the hang of AoE kiting.  
<br />

<br />
The AK dropped jack and crap btw. 
<br />

<br />
A couple points on the above.  The first post mentioned hailing Gamesh. It's my understanding that Gamesh only hands out the XP version of the sewer trials not the ones for advancement.  You need to hail the high priest for the trial to count towards advancement. 
<br />

<br />
Also, on the post about having to go back and hail Anshara again, I hailed Anshura on the way down.  I got the message about receiving the character flag on killing the AK.  I did not hail Anshura afterwards.  I used a gate potion to get out rather than just quitting the expedition thinking that I would go back and hail Anshura from the entrance.  I changed my mind and just went straight to the high priest.  I quit the expedition but when I hailed the high priest again he gave the expedition to the crematory trial.  I'm wondering if some of your group members were invised the first time they tried hailing Anshura and didn't get the pre-flag.  
<br />

<br />
For anyone thinking about soloing this, it's really pretty easy.  There's only a couple of tricks. The first is getting there which is basically just lull/invis.  The other is staying clear of agroing the roamer once you start kiting the stonemites/AK. On the other hand, I'm not sure how much good it does you to solo this trial other than good bragging rights.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />  
