<br />

<br />
I was the only member of my group who already had the Sewer 1 flag.
<br />

<br />
My group was extremely ticked, so I loaded up my chants and told them I was going to try to solo the 9 aged stonemites and the AK.  They laughed at first, but they slowly realized it was doable as I killed more and more of the aged stonemites.
<br />

<br />
The aged kites took upwards of 8 minutes each, give or take a few minutes depending on whether I was trying to 5-chant + Assonance at the time, and whether it was working well.  I have JF3, IM4, and a TDrum.  This is pretty much in line with what previous posters have said, I think.
<br />

<br />
Having only RS4 I was able to keep ahead of the mites fairly well, though I did get caught a few times.  The boss actually caught me twice:  once right after he spawned (I used deftdance), and later when he had 8% health left.  Luckily he only hit me twice the second time.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, he died, and had no loot at all on his corpse.  My groupmates (who had been sitting at the ZI goofing off for the last hour) let out cries of joy and ran off to line up some permanent flags with the priest and scribe.
<br />

<br />
I also got about 50% AA exp from soloing the 9 aged mites and the AK.
<br />

<br />
It was a pretty good night all in all. =)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
